outlook /ˈaʊtˌlʊk/

(outlooks) 

1. N-COUNT Your outlook is your general attitude toward life. 人生观 [usu sing, with supp, also 'in' N] 

例： I adopted a positive outlook on life. 我选择了一种积极的人生观。 

2. N-SING The outlook for something is what people think will happen in relation to it. 前景 

例： The economic outlook is one of rising unemployment. 经济前景恶化，失业率不断增长。

